name: Skillet Lasagna from Land O'Lakes®
description: Take the fuss out of lasagna with this quick and easy stove-top recipe starting with flavorful Sauté Express® Sauté Starter.
recipeIngredient: 6 ounces uncooked dried mafalda (mini lasagna noodles) or bowtie pasta
2 squares Land O'Lakes® Italian Herb Saute Express®

recipeInstructions.text: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain; set aside.
Melt Saute Express® squares in 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat just until bubbles begin to form.
Place ground beef into skillet. Cook 4 to 6 minutes or until browned. (Do not drain beef.)
Add spinach and diced tomatoes. Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until spinach is wilted and heated through. Add cooked pasta. Stir until well mixed.
Sprinkle with cheese. Continue cooking, without stirring, 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

review.reviewBody: I have made this recipe and maybe it beats the purpose of land o' lakes product.. but I simply used Olive oil, season salt, lemon pepper, poultry seasoning, and heated up on the stove in a frying pan for about 5 min.. and I added all fresh herbs.. parsley ,basil, Italian herb and stirred.. I then added the ground Chuck and continued with canned roasted tomatoes and spinach. I also added the mozzarella cheese shredded and stirred again.. I added a few more herbs on the top and baked 5 min.. this was a hit in my house! easy to make and fulfilling.. I said next time I will add asparagus tips!

I've made this two times and I loved it!  I did cook the ground beef and drain it though.  Years and years of cooking will not let me skip this step.  I was worried it wouldn't have enough liquid so I wound up adding sliced mushrooms as they make their own liquid (I'm sure this was more of a mental thing but I like mushroons so it works).  I found Barilla Plus Bowtie Pasta and it was wonderful. The first time I made it, I kept searching for more of a tomato-y taste and I considered using tomato sauce but then I realized that was silly because I didn't want to hide the Land O'Lakes flavor so I used stewed tomatoes and it was delicious!  When I used pre-shredded mozzarella, it wound up being stringy at first, leftovers it wasn't stringy but I don't know who would cook this and wait to eat it the next day.  I am going to try the little mozzarella balls next.  Anyway, I loved how quickly this came together, I loved all the vegetables (with the mushrooms that's three different colored veggies), and I loved the flavor.  I'm going to try the Garlic and Herb next!

I wouldn't bother putting spinach in the pasta because it was over powered by the other tastes. But the meat and nuddles worked well together. If your looking for a good pasta recipe I recommend this one and if your like me and don't like spinach you can make it your own.
